Sprinkle each fillet with juice and pepper. Arrange broccoli spears on narrow end of each fish fillet; roll up. Secure with toothpicks. Place, seam-side down, in 10x6-inch microwavable baking dish; cover. Microwave on HIGH 5 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Microwave remaining ingredients in small microwavable bowl 2 to 3 minutes or until sauce is smooth, stirring after each minute. Remove toothpicks before serving. Serve with sauce.